    <thetext>Usually, the spec formats Notes like paragraphs, with all lines flush-left.
But in:
   12.4.4.1  Static Semantics: Early Errors
   12.13.5.1 Static Semantics: Early Errors
   13.6.4.1  Static Semantics: Early Errors
each has a Note where:
(a) the word &quot;NOTE&quot; is slightly indented; and
(b) subsequent lines are significantly indented.

(Of course, in 12.4.4.1, the second line is code, so indenting it is fine, but the third line should be flush-left.)</thetext>
